.TH RAISE 3  1995-08-31 "GNU" "Linux Programmer's Manual"
.SH NAME
raise \- send a signal to the current process
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <signal.h>
.sp
.BI "int raise(int " sig );
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The 
.B raise()
function sends a signal to the current process.
It is equivalent to
.sp
.RS
.BI "kill(getpid(), " "sig" );
.RE
.SH "RETURN VALUE"
0 on success, nonzero for failure.
.SH "CONFORMING TO"
ANSI\-C
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR getpid (2),
.BR kill (2),
.BR signal (2)
